<paragraph id="9A7736F2AF4FB060804B96FDFDC2FB0D" blockId="15.[264,1324,399,1464]" box="[312,514,1238,1264]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Host: Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9A7736F2AF4FB060804B96D5FE6EFA45" blockId="15.[264,1324,399,1464]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Discussion: This is the largest and arguably the most striking of Central American 
<taxonomicName id="5DC84D71AF4FB060807B970CFE47FABD" box="[264,391,1319,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A8BCEAE0AF4FB060807B970CFE47FABD" box="[264,391,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Paragrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="45738850AF4FB06080AD970DFD83FABD" box="[478,579,1318,1344]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">paratype</typeStatus>
is also 
<quantity id="5D309B17AF4FB06083D4970DFCC5FABD" box="[679,773,1318,1344]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
in length and may be a female. It was first thought to be 
<taxonomicName id="5DC84D71AF4FB06080C89764FDF3FA95" box="[443,563,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevicollis">
<emphasis id="A8BCEAE0AF4FB06080C89764FDF3FA95" box="[443,563,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">laevicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but direct comparison with the 
<typeStatus id="45738850AF4FB06082A19765FBC5FA95" box="[978,1029,1358,1384]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
of that species showed 
<taxonomicName id="5DC84D71AF4FB060807B975CFEA2FA6D" box="[264,354,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Paragrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azureus">
<emphasis id="A8BCEAE0AF4FB060807B975CFEA2FA6D" box="[264,354,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">azureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be larger, differently colored, the pronotum more heavily punctate, and different in other ways.
</paragraph>
